events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Ron Holland II scored 14 of his season-high 26 points in the fourth quarter, and the Detroit Pistons beat CJ McCollum and the New Orleans Pelicans 136-130 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Holland has big final quarter and scores season-high 26 points to lead Pistons over Pelicans 136-130

headlines.description: — Jarrett Allen scored 18 points and Donovan Mitchell added 16, helping Cleveland snap a four-game losing streak with a 120-91 victory over the Utah Jazz on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavaliers snap 4-game skid with 120-91 victory over Jazz

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 28 points with 12 assists, Zaccharie Risacher scored 22 points and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Philadelphia 76ers 132-119 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trae Young, Zaccharie Risacher lead Hawks to 132-119 win over 76ers

headlines.description: — Andrew Wiggins scored 42 points for the second-highest scoring game of his career, Tyler Herro added 29 and the Miami Heat beat the Charlotte Hornets 122-105 on Sunday night to snap a 10-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wiggins scores 42 points and Heat roll past Hornets 122-105 to snap 10-game losing streak

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Devin Vassell scored 25 points, Julian Champagnie had 20 and the San Antonio Spurs won their third straight game by routing the Toronto Raptors 123-89 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vassell scores 25 as Spurs rout slumping Raptors 123-89 for third straight win, fifth in seven

events.name: Boston Celtics at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 30 points, nine assists and nine rebounds and the Boston Celtics extended their winning streak to five games with a 129-116 win over the Portland Trail Blazers on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics extend their winning streak to 5 games with a 129-116 win over Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray had 39 points, Michael Porter Jr. added 17 points and nine rebounds and the Denver Nuggets beat Houston 116-111 on Sunday night to snap the Rockets' nine-game win streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jamal Murray scores 39 points to lift Denver to 116-111 win over Houston

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 26 points and eight assists, Aaron Wiggins scored 19 points and the NBA-leading Oklahoma City Thunder extended their winning streak to six games by holding on to beat the Los Angeles Clippers 103-101 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 26 as Thunder beat Clippers 103-101 for 6th straight victory
